data.label:
Narrator

I looked out the window as the noise of the city diminished, and saw that we were already inside the Palace complex.

Narrator

The Maroon Palace stood on a small hilltop surrounded by trees. We passed by the palace and entered the forest that separated it from the Grand National Assembly.

Narrator

The complex housed the buildings of all government branches in the centre of Holsord. It was one of the biggest developments in Sordland.

Player

"Hey, Serge. I'm okay. How are you doing?"

Serge Wolkner

"I'm as good as I can be, sir."

Narrator

Serge made a left turn out the forest and entered the vast garden area of the Assembly.

Player

"Slow down, Serge. Are you sure?"

Serge Wolkner

"I'm sure you'll meet him, sir. If he's coming here after all these years, he would pay the President his respects."

Player

"He's probably here to make a scene."

Narrator

He tried to get Gloria's attention by waving at her.

Narrator

Serge drove inside the gates of the parkway and parked the car.

Player

"We'll talk later. See you, Serge."

Gloria Tory

"Thereby, the Grand National Assembly has rejected the changes to the Constitution."

Narrator

The door opened to reveal vast corridors of wood and white stone. I joined the crowd of people who were walking slowly towards the parliamentary hall.

Lucian Galade

"Ah, sir. There you are. Have you seen Vice President Vectern? He's nowhere to be found."

Player

"I don't think he'll miss a vote this important..."

Narrator

He pointed at the back of the Assembly, near one of the exits.

Lucian Galade

"I hope you are right."

Lucian Galade

"I hope Mr. Vectern arrives soon too..."

Lucian Galade

"At any rate, how about yourself? Are you ready to finally face the Assembly, sir?"

Player

"As ready as I've ever been, Lucian."

Player

"Yes. I hope it works out."

Serge Wolkner

"My father would be happy."

Lucian Galade

"We'll address that later, sir. Come, we must go inside."

Lucian Galade

"I have full confidence in you, Mr. President."

Narrator

He opened his hand and showed me a very old-looking pocket watch. It looked like it was made during the Century of Revolutions.

Narrator

I waited as the MPs took their places inside the hall one by one.

Narrator

After a short while, everybody was in their seats.

Gloria Tory

"According to the current Constitution, constitutional amendments require a two-thirds majority in order to reach Assembly approval."

Gloria Tory

"If the vote succeeds, the proposal will be sent to the Supreme Court."

Gloria Tory

"The proposal in question includes these points..."

Gloria Tory

"First section of the changes... Article 57 is modified with the following..."

Petr Vectern

"I mean... Maybe I was not in this exact seat, sure... But I was here in the Assembly."

Gloria Tory

"...may not exercise his right to..."

Narrator

Most of the MPs seemed like they were already falling asleep.

Narrator

The seat was really hurting my back.

Gloria Tory

"136 ayes. 40 more votes to count."

Player

"No, you were not. I was here until the voting began."

Player

"LADIES AND GENTLEMEN! VOTE NOW FOR THE FUTURE OF SORDLAND!"

Gloria Tory

"As I previously stated, it will require a two-thirds majority in order to pass..."

Gloria Tory

"You may now cast your votes."

Narrator

I felt the need to stand up and stretch. I looked down at the hall from the platform I was seated on.

Player_Italic

I sat down and kept watching the Assembly.

Sit back down and keep watching.

RemoveConversant(Gloria Tory); WaitForMessage(Continue);

Petr Vectern

"Our best bet to divide the Old Guard votes is Garaci. He's the most corrupt person I've ever known."

Narrator

My voice echoed in the hall. Everybody turned and looked at me with surprise.

Player

"Let's enjoy this victory for now."

Narrator

Gloria raised an eyebrow when she saw me.

Player

"Orso Hawker will be a problem."

Narrator

Some USP members started to whistle and clap while others gave me puzzled looks.

Gloria Tory

"117 ayes. 50 more votes to count."

Narrator

After regathering our thoughts, Petr and I walked out of the Assembly hall.

Narrator

Some of the members in the hall started to shout back at me.

Gloria Tory

"Ladies and Gentlemen of the Assembly! We will soon begin counting. Please cast your votes if you haven't already."

Narrator

We both looked down at the floor for a while.

Player

"YOU WILL DO AS I SAY!"

Player

"Mr. Soll, welcome to the Assembly!"

Gloria Tory

"Gentlemen! Please! Don't you know how to cast a vote? This is not a circus!"

Narrator

Some MPs started shouting back at Gloria.

Narrator

She kept hitting the gavel frantically.

Gloria Tory

"Ladies and gentlemen! Please have civil conversations and refrain from shouting at each other! If you are not capable of that, please leave the Assembly!"

Gloria Tory

"Also, Mr. President. Please refrain from shouting yourself. If you want to share something with the Assembly, please ask to speak after the vote session is concluded."

Gloria Tory

"Thereby, the Grand National Assembly has reached a two-thirds majority and accepted the changes to the Constitution."

Petr Vectern

"It's hard to be in charge without any support... well, let's see what happens."

Gloria Tory

"Don't worry. There is already a time limit and we are abiding by the rules. Assembly members are used to this process."

Narrator

I saw some people cast their votes, but many were still walking around the hall or talking to each other.

Narrator

He stopped below the mezzanine and looked up at me.

Petr Vectern

"You are right... So you think we can still survive this?"

Player_Italic

I went down to the floor and approached Kesaro.

Go down to talk to him.

(BaseGame.Reform_Albin_Convinced == true && BaseGame.Reform_BludishRights_Amendment_Proposal == false) || (BaseGame.Reform_BludishRights_Amendment_Proposal == true && BaseGame.Amendment_USP_Gloria_Convinced == true)

nan

Player_Italic

I stared back down at him.

Stare at him.

Kesaro Kibener

"Mr. President! How are you feeling up there? Are you comfortable?"

Player

"Screw Soll and the party. We were always on our own."

Narrator

He looked much older than he had five years ago. But I could tell he had the same fire in him. Some MP's had already gathered around him and were chattering in awe.

Kesaro Kibener

"You were once sitting among us in the Assembly, working under the Soll administration... Don't ever forget your past."

Kesaro Kibener

"You seem to be fond of your position. Try to enjoy it while you can."

Albin Clavin

"I'm sorry to take so long, Mr. President. There was a *friend* who needed more clarification for his vote."

Petr Vectern

"In any case, the proposal has passed the Assembly. But now we have to think about the Supreme Court..."

Narrator

Suddenly, I saw Lucian waving at me. He was among a group of people gathered in the hall.

Lucian Galade

"I doubt that, sir. I think he's here to sabotage the vote by sheer force of personality."

Kesaro Kibener

"Mr. President! How are you feeling about the vote?"

Player

"We can't change the Constitution, so what? We are still in charge."

Player

"Not so fast. We still have the Court to pass."

Petr Vectern

"What the hell was that?"

Albin Clavin

"Let's get this over with, gentlemen."

Kesaro Kibener

"You know I can't do that. We have already stated our decision."

Narrator

The Assembly gradually went quiet as people started to notice Soll's presence in the hall.

Kesaro Kibener

"That's the right feeling. This whole proposal is a mistake."

Kesaro Kibener

"The best outcome for this proposal is failure."

Kesaro Kibener

"Even knowing you don't have our support? How optimistic of you."

Kesaro Kibener

"I have lost my respect for you, Mr. Rayne. So many problems in Sordland that must be addressed, and yet you insist on stalling us with your 'democratic' reforms..."

Albin Clavin

"I'm surprised to see you here, considering the way you ignored your own party. Don't worry, Mr. President. We are here. Relax."

Kesaro Kibener

"I hope to be there when it happens."

Narrator

He gestured at the men behind him.

Gloria Tory

"Thereby, the Grand National Assembly has surpassed a two-thirds majority and accepted the changes to the Constitution."

Player

"We have to make sure he doesn't sabotage anything."

Albin Clavin

"I'm sorry, Mr. President. We had an issue with one vote at the last minute. I've collected them all now."

Player_Italic

I went to the very center of the hall to shout at the crowd of people who still hadn't cast their votes.

Shout at the Assembly from the center of the hall.

Narrator

Then I saw Lucian waving at me. He was among a group of people in the corner of the hall. I walked up to him.

Frens Ricter

"It is time to realize that real change will only come from real reformists. The People's Freedom and Justice Party will keep leading this movement!"

Mansoun Leke

"I wish you good luck with the vote."

BaseGame.Reform_Law_Threshold_3 == true && BaseGame.Reform_Law_Threshold_8 == true && BaseGame.Reform_VoteCount_Independents_1 == true

nan

Player

"Just cast your votes and let the counting begin."

Mansoun Leke

"If this succeeds, this will finally open the way for Bludish representation in the Assembly. We'll have you to thank for that."

Player_Italic

I called out to him.

Call out to him.

!((BaseGame.Reform_Albin_Convinced == true && BaseGame.Reform_BludishRights_Amendment_Proposal == false) || (BaseGame.Reform_BludishRights_Amendment_Proposal == true && BaseGame.Amendment_USP_Gloria_Convinced == true))

nan

Mansoun Leke

"I'm also 100 percent behind your decision to abolish the Member of Honor position. At last, a chance to hold Tarquin Soll accountable for what he did to the Bludish people..."

Mansoun Leke

"You have my support. I'd like to also see you support Bludish rights in the future. I hope you stand by us."

Petr Vectern

"Thank God he didn't do anything..."

Narrator

He walked out the exit as two of his guards held the doors for him.

Gloria Tory

"The voting has been concluded."

Mansoun Leke

"Today is a big day for you, after all."

Narrator

He stood and gazed around the hall as all of the members of the Grand National Assembly went silent.

Player

"It's a big day for all of us."

Player

"I hope I have your support, Mr. Leke."

Player

"I need the independents to make it bigger."

Gloria Tory

"Oh, by the way, we have 251 members today. As you can see, the Member of Honor is here. He has already cast his vote."

Mansoun Leke

"Even though we feel it doesn't address the issues we care about the most, it is still a step in the right direction."

Mansoun Leke

"But I have to say... we were disappointed when we first read the proposal."

Gloria Tory

"The proposal has 179 ayes and 72 nays."

Player

"Thank you for the nice words. You have my support too."

Player

"Thank you. But I don't think the Bludish people are facing as many problems as in the past."

Mansoun Leke

"The problems might not be identical, but they are still there, Mr. President. Don't presume to know what the Bludish people are facing."

Lucian Galade

"Has he, now. So, Mrs. Tory, how many votes are missing?"

Mansoun Leke

"I hope you stand by your words, Mr. President."

Mansoun Leke

"Anyway, I've got to go cast my vote."

Lucian Galade

"I would advise against that right now. The Assembly must focus on the vote. Any confrontation between the two of you would draw their attention away."

Gloria Tory

"Gentlemen. Why don't you go back to your seats? Let's follow the procedure."

Player

"We have done our best, Mr. Leke."

Frens Ricter

"He's just like his predecessors -- enjoying the privilege of the presidency while ignoring the responsibility that comes with it!"

Player

"We didn't write it to get votes from the independents."

Mansoun Leke

"No. You wrote it for the people of Sordland. Some of them, anyway."

Mansoun Leke

"I've got to go cast my vote."

Narrator

He bowed in front of Soll and gave him a military salute.

Frens Ricter

"The President and the USP got what they deserved! This proposal was doomed from the start."

BaseGame.Relations_Frens_Bribed == true || BaseGame.Relations_Frens_Promise_Taurus == true || BaseGame.Relations_Frens_Promise_Seat == true

nan

Lucian Galade

"Sir, did you vote yet? We have to be quick."

Narrator

I signed my vote and prepared the envelope. Together, Lucian and I walked to the center of the hall to cast our votes. He kept rushing me throughout the process.

Narrator

Gloria bowed her head slightly in respect as she saw us vote. Lucian pulled on my arm and whispered in my ear.

Gloria Tory

"The proposal has 167 ayes and 84 nays."

Player

"Let's just go back to our seats. Any noise we make will distract everyone further."

Lucian Galade

"Maybe you can address him after the vote."

Lucian Galade

"When I waved at you, he was in the corridors. He must be somewhere inside the hall now."

Lucian Galade

"You have to accelerate the voting process. We need everybody to vote as soon as possible."

Frens Ricter

"I want to congratulate the members of the Assembly and the President for finally passing changes to our dusty old Constitution!"

Lucian Galade

"We should refrain from giving him the spotlight he expects."

Lucian Galade

"We don't know what he's capable of right now. But if Assembly members see him, he might influence them against the proposal."

Lucian Galade

"If that's what you wish."

Player

"Maybe he's here to support me."

Player

"We should make people vote now!"

Kesaro Kibener

"How are you feeling about the vote?"

Kesaro Kibener

"Of course. I did promise that."

Narrator

He gave me a cold stare.

Narrator

Petr pointed at where Frens Ricter was sitting.

Petr Vectern

"Looks like Kesaro over there is in our corner."

Narrator

Petr pointed at where Kesaro Kibener was sitting.

Narrator

Petr pointed at where Frens Ricter was sitting.

Petr Vectern

"Look at Kesaro over there. I'm sure he was behind this mess. You shouldn't have trusted him."

Player

"You're right. I knew I couldn't trust him."

Player

"It's not over yet, Petr. Don't jump to conclusions."

Player

"To be honest, I don't really like him."

Player

"He never really supported us, though. It's surprising."

Gloria Tory

"The proposal has only 70 ayes and did not even gather a simple majority."

Gloria Tory

"The proposal has 225 ayes and 26 nays. A historic result."

Narrator

He straightened his tie and walked away.

Gloria Tory

"The proposal has 166 ayes and 85 nays."

Narrator

I heard a chorus of angry outbursts coming from the USP seats.

Petr Vectern

"...I know. This just happened."

Petr Vectern

"It looks like Gloria screwed us over..."

Serge Wolkner

"I overheard several men talking about it around the gardens of the Assembly, sir. I'm not sure who they were."

Serge Wolkner

"You know better than I do, sir."

Gloria Tory

"Unfortunately, the proposal in question was altered after it was reviewed by the Assembly."

Gloria Tory

"Therefore, I have to go over each of the points again."

Mansoun Leke

"Today is a big day."

Mansoun Leke

"Let's win this together, shall we?"

Player
